This July 4th, take your dessert to the next level with Chessmen Banana Pudding 🎆

Ingredients
2 packages (7.25oz) Pepperidge Farm® Chessmen® Butter Cookies
1.5 cups (12oz.) Milk
½ cup (4oz.) Sweetened Condensed Milk
1 package (about 3.4 ounces) instant vanilla pudding and pie filling mix
3 cup heavy cream
3 large bananas, sliced

Instructions: 
In a bowl, whisk milk and sweetened condensed milk 
Prepare pudding according to the pack using the milk and sweetened condensed milk mixture
Add the heavy cream to a separate bowl and whisk with an electric mixer at medium speed until stiff peaks form, do not overmix
Whisk 2/3 of the whipped cream into the pudding mix and stir until fully combined
To assemble, arrange 9 cookies in the bottom of an 8x8x2-inch baking dish; Arrange enough bananas to cover the cookies.
Add one quarter of the pudding and spread over the bananas, repeat this process two more times
Garnish the top layer with the remaining whipped cream and evenly place 9 of remaining cookies on top
Cover the baking dish and refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight
